verses.text: And Moses answered and said , But, behold, they will not believe me, nor hearken unto my voice : for they will say , The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath not appeared unto thee.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto him, What \add is\add* that in thine hand ? And he said , A rod.
And he said , Cast it on the ground. And he cast it on the ground , and it became a serpent ; and Moses fled from before it.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , Put forth thine hand , and take it by the tail. And he put forth his hand , and caught it, and it became a rod in his hand :
That they may believe that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of their fathers , the God of Abraham , the God of Isaac , and the God of Jacob , hath appeared unto thee. \p

¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said furthermore unto him, Put now thine hand into thy bosom. And he put his hand into his bosom : and when he took it out, behold, his hand \add was\add* leprous as snow.
And he said , Put thine hand into thy bosom again. And he put his hand into his bosom again ; and plucked it out of his bosom , and, behold, it was turned again as his \add other\add* flesh.
And it shall come to pass, if they will not believe thee, neither hearken to the voice of the first sign , that they will believe the voice of the latter sign.

And it shall come to pass, if they will not believe also these two signs , neither hearken unto thy voice , that thou shalt take of the water of the river , and pour \add it\add* upon the dry \add land:\add* and the water which thou takest out of the river shall become blood upon the dry \add land\add*.\f + \fr 4.9 \ft shall become: Heb. shall be and shall be\f* \p

¶ And Moses said unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, O my Lord , I \add am\add* not eloquent , neither heretofore , nor since thou hast spoken unto thy servant : but I \add am\add* slow of speech , and of a slow tongue.\f + \fr 4.10 \ft eloquent: Heb. a man of words\f*\f + \fr 4.10 \ft heretofore: Heb. since yesterday, nor since the third day\f*

And the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* said unto him, Who hath made man’s mouth ? or who maketh the dumb , or deaf , or the seeing , or the blind ? have not I the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*?
Now therefore go , and I will be with thy mouth , and teach thee what thou shalt say.
And he said , O my Lord , send , I pray thee, by the hand \add of him whom\add* thou wilt send.\f + \fr 4.13 \ft wilt: or, shouldest\f*

And the anger of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* was kindled against Moses , and he said , \add Is\add* not Aaron the Levite thy brother ? I know that he can speak well. And also, behold, he cometh forth to meet thee: and when he seeth thee, he will be glad in his heart.
And thou shalt speak unto him, and put words in his mouth : and I will be with thy mouth , and with his mouth , and will teach you what ye shall do.
And he shall be thy spokesman unto the people : and he shall be, \add even\add* he shall be to thee instead of a mouth , and thou shalt be to him instead of God.
And thou shalt take this rod in thine hand , wherewith thou shalt do signs. \p

¶ And Moses went and returned to Jethro his father in law , and said unto him, Let me go , I pray thee, and return unto my brethren which \add are\add* in Egypt , and see whether they be yet alive. And Jethro said to Moses , Go in peace.\f + \fr 4.18 \ft Jethro: Heb. Jether\f*
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses in Midian , Go , return into Egypt : for all the men are dead which sought thy life.
And Moses took his wife and his sons , and set them upon an ass , and he returned to the land of Egypt : and Moses took the rod of God in his hand.

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , When thou goest to return into Egypt , see that thou do all those wonders before Pharaoh , which I have put in thine hand : but I will harden his heart , that he shall not let the people go.
And thou shalt say unto Pharaoh , Thus saith the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, Israel \add is\add* my son , \add even\add* my firstborn :
And I say unto thee, Let my son go , that he may serve me: and if thou refuse to let him go , behold, I will slay thy son , \add even\add* thy firstborn. \p
¶ And it came to pass by the way in the inn , that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* met him, and sought to kill him.

Then Zipporah took a sharp stone , and cut off the foreskin of her son , and cast \add it\add* at his feet , and said , Surely a bloody husband \add art\add* thou to me.\f + \fr 4.25 \ft sharp…: or, knife\f*\f + \fr 4.25 \ft cast…: Heb. made it touch\f*
So he let him go : then she said , A bloody husband \add thou art\add*, because of the circumcision. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said to Aaron , Go into the wilderness to meet Moses. And he went , and met him in the mount of God , and kissed him.
And Moses told Aaron all the words of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* who had sent him, and all the signs which he had commanded him. \p
¶ And Moses and Aaron went and gathered together all the elders of the children of Israel :
And Aaron spake all the words which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had spoken unto Moses , and did the signs in the sight of the people.

And the people believed : and when they heard that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* had visited the children of Israel , and that he had looked upon their affliction , then they bowed their heads and worshipped.
